<u>Ankle Displacement Measures </u>
The following measures should be taken using a dicom viewer based on AP, lateral and mortise views of post-operative xrays.

10. <u>Coronal plane displacement-</u> the distance between a vertical line along the lateral edge of the lateral talus compared to a vertical line perpendicular to the anterolateral edge of the distal tibia

9. <u>Coronal plane displacement-</u> the distance between a vertical line along the lateral edge of the lateral talus compared to a vertical line perpendicular to the anterolateral edge of the distal tibia

11. <u>Talar tilt displacement-</u> the angle between lines parallel to the distal tibia plafond and the superior talar dome. Talar tilt will also be defined as Varus or Valgus per current convention of direction of talus in reference to the distal tibia.

10. <u>Talar tilt displacement-</u> the angle between lines parallel to the distal tibia plafond and the superior talar dome. Talar tilt will also be defined as Varus or Valgus per current convention of direction of talus in reference to the distal tibia.
12. <u>Sagittal displacement-</u> The distance between a vertical line through the center of the tibia and a center of a circle drawn to match the center of rotation of the talar dome.
11. <u>Sagittal displacement-</u> The distance between a vertical line through the center of the tibia and a center of a circle drawn to match the center of rotation of the talar dome.

<u>Tibia Plateau Displacement Measures</u>
The following measures should be taken using a dicom viewer of AP and Lateral Post-Operative x-rays:
13.  <u>Condylar width</u>- The widest measure from medial to lateral plateau edge on AP xray.
12.  <u>Condylar width</u>- The widest measure from medial to lateral plateau edge on AP xray.
14. <u>Difference in height between medial and lateral plateaus-</u> The difference between line parallel to medial and lateral plateaus on AP xray
13a. <u>Difference in height between medial and lateral plateaus-</u> The difference between line parallel to medial and lateral plateaus on AP xray
13b. Which is higher, the medial or lateral plateau?
15a. Angle between the femur and the tibia - The angle between a line through the center of the tibia and center of the femur

14a. Angle between the femur and the tibia - The angle between a line through the center of the tibia and center of the femur. (For values less < 90 degrees, select varus. For values > 90 degrees, select valgus.)
15b. <u>Medial Proximal Tibia Angle (MPTA):</U> Angle between line down Center of tibia and line parallel to proximal tibia plateau
14b. <u>Medial Proximal Tibia Angle (MPTA):</U> Angle between line down Center of tibia and line parallel to proximal tibia plateau
15c. <u>Sagittal plane alignment of proximal tibia- </u> The angle between a line perpendicular to the shaft of the tibia and the posterior slope of the proximal tibia.
14c. <u>Sagittal plane alignment of proximal tibia- </u> The angle between a line perpendicular to the shaft of the tibia and the posterior slope of the proximal tibia.

12. Were radiographs taken since last study visit?
14. Record the degree of talus tilt and medial and lateral malleolus displacement measuring the distance between talar dome to distal tibia articular surface on radiographs taken at follow-up.

<u>Ankle Displacement Measures </u>
The following measures should be taken using a dicom viewer based on AP, lateral and mortise views of post-operative xrays

14a. <u>Coronal plane displacement-</u> the distance between a vertical line along the lateral edge of the lateral talus compared to a vertical line perpendicular to the anterolateral edge of the distal tibia

14b. <u>Talar tilt displacement-</u> the angle between lines parallel to the distal tibia plafond and the superior talar dome. Talar tilt will also be defined as Varus or Valgus per current convention of direction of talus in reference to the distal tibia.
14c. <u>Sagittal displacement-</u> The distance between a vertical line through the center of the tibia and a center of a circle drawn to match the center of rotation of the talar dome.

<u>Tibia Plateau Displacement Measures</u>
The following measures should be taken using a dicom viewer of AP and Lateral Post-Operative x-rays:
14d.  <u>Condylar width</u>- The widest measure from medial to lateral plateau edge on AP xray.
14e.<u>Difference in height between medial and lateral plateaus-</u> The difference between line parallel to medial and lateral plateaus on AP xray
Which is higher, the medial or lateral plateau?

14f. Angle between the femur and the tibia - The angle between a line through the center of the tibia and center of the femur. (For values less < 90 degrees, select varus. For values > 90 degrees, select valgus.)
14g.  <u>Medial Proximal Tibia Angle (MPTA):</U> Angle between line down Center of tibia and line parallel to proximal tibia plateau
14h. <u>Sagittal plane alignment of proximal tibia- </u> The angle between a line perpendicular to the shaft of the tibia and the posterior slope of the proximal tibia.
14i. <u>Articular step-off</u>  If there is articular step-off present, indicate the largest measure on AP and lateral xrays.
14j. Is patella centered on the AP xray?
14k. <u>Overlap of fibula of tibia on AP xrays-</u> on a scale of 0 to 100%
